After all these years,

14
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,530
I finally plucked up my courage...

15
00:02:42,159 --> 00:02:44,319
for the first time...

16
00:02:45,240 --> 00:02:46,719
to call you Yu Jie.

17
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:51,120
I remember,

18
00:02:51,879 --> 00:02:53,560
when we first got married,

19
00:02:55,400 --> 00:02:57,080
I bought you the white outfit...

20
00:02:58,840 --> 00:03:00,479
in this painting.

21
00:03:02,280 --> 00:03:03,439
Do you remember?

22
00:03:07,520 --> 00:03:11,439
I kept this painting of yours in the basement of my villa...

23
00:03:11,439 --> 00:03:14,479
because I was too scared to face this moment.

24
00:03:14,879 --> 00:03:16,159
I can't face you.

25
00:03:19,080 --> 00:03:20,080
Yu Jie.

26
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,840
If I didn't argue with you back then,

27
00:03:27,840 --> 00:03:30,520
you wouldn't have run away with our son.

28
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,439
You also wouldn't have...

29
00:03:33,719 --> 00:03:35,520
fallen into the water in the car.

30
00:03:38,360 --> 00:03:41,120
If I acted like a real man...

31
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:45,120
and went to hug and embrace you,

32
00:03:46,960 --> 00:03:49,319
nothing would have happened.

33
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:50,960
Yu Jie...

34
00:03:52,840 --> 00:03:54,960
It's all my fault.

35
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,879
I let you and our son down.

36
00:04:01,879 --> 00:04:04,439
My life...

37
00:04:06,319 --> 00:04:08,599
is only full of regrets.

38
00:04:08,599 --> 00:04:10,680
I've let everyone down.

39
00:04:11,280 --> 00:04:14,159
I thought everything I did was right.

40
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:15,879
But now, it looks like...

41
00:04:17,170 --> 00:04:18,879
everything I did...

42
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:25,279
was all wrong.

43
00:04:32,050 --> 00:04:34,279
It was all wrong.

44
00:04:34,279 --> 00:04:35,279
Don't be sad.

45
00:04:35,480 --> 00:04:37,480
All right.

46
00:04:37,610 --> 00:04:38,610
Get up.

47
00:05:02,610 --> 00:05:03,959
I misunderstood my dad this whole time.

48
00:05:10,639 --> 00:05:11,800
Why do you say that?

49
00:05:24,959 --> 00:05:27,079
He actually loved my mom very much.

50
00:05:28,319 --> 00:05:29,600
He loves you very much too.

51
00:05:49,199 --> 00:05:51,240
Mr. Hou, it's time to eat.

52
00:05:53,079 --> 00:05:54,079
I'm coming.

53
00:06:07,199 --> 00:06:08,399
Did you not call Hou Jue?

54
00:06:12,160 --> 00:06:13,160
He...

55
00:06:14,399 --> 00:06:15,519
Come on. Don't worry.

56
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:17,000
You'll know once you sit down.

57
00:06:17,000 --> 00:06:18,480
Come, sit down.

58
00:06:19,560 --> 00:06:21,279
Why is he in the kitchen?

59
00:06:23,399 --> 00:06:24,800
You'll see.

60
00:06:30,519 --> 00:06:31,519
Be careful.

61
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:35,439
Guess what this is.

62
00:06:37,319 --> 00:06:38,920
What are you guys up to?

63
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,560
Open it.

64
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:43,560
Your son personally made this for you.

65
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,160
All right, let me do it.

66
00:06:49,839 --> 00:06:51,879
Here, that's enough. I'll do it.

67
00:06:56,480 --> 00:06:58,360
This braised pork belly smells good.

68
00:07:00,759 --> 00:07:03,680
My son knows braised pork belly is my favorite.

69
00:07:03,800 --> 00:07:05,759
Here, let's eat.

70
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:14,040
I have to eat this sparingly.

71
00:07:28,839 --> 00:07:29,839
Hou Jue.

72
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:34,439
Actually, I fed you when you were very young.

73
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:36,639
Let me feed you again today.

74
00:07:38,120 --> 00:07:39,839
There are only a few pieces. There's no more.

75
00:07:41,279 --> 00:07:42,600
You can only eat this once a week.

76
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:46,240
Leave the fatty parts for me.

77
00:07:46,560 --> 00:07:47,560
You can eat the lean meat.

78
00:07:47,879 --> 00:07:49,439
- Won't you be upset? - Not at all.

79
00:07:50,079 --> 00:07:51,120
Then here I go.

80
00:07:55,839 --> 00:07:57,079
It's not so good this time.

81
00:07:57,560 --> 00:07:58,879
I didn't do a good job.

82
00:07:59,560 --> 00:08:01,000
It's not bad. It's already pretty good.

83
00:08:01,120 --> 00:08:02,120
- Here. - Come on, let's eat.

84
00:08:07,800 --> 00:08:08,839
It's good, right?

85
00:08:20,519 --> 00:08:22,680
We usually teach in small groups here.

86
00:08:22,839 --> 00:08:24,240
In order to guarantee the quality of learning,

87
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,079
there are a maximum of six students in each class.

88
00:08:26,319 --> 00:08:27,639
Our instructors are all excellent.

89
00:08:27,759 --> 00:08:29,120
They're all professional team retirees.

90
00:08:29,240 --> 00:08:31,759
Take me for example. Our skills are definitely good.

91
00:08:32,480 --> 00:08:33,840
We also have private lessons.

92
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:35,600
We charge by the hour, but it's a little expensive.

93
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:38,960
Do you not know how to swim at all?

94
00:08:39,879 --> 00:08:41,120
I could when I was young.

95
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:42,600
I could swim when I was eight.

96
00:08:43,330 --> 00:08:44,330
It's okay.

97
00:08:44,450 --> 00:08:46,279
Give it a try. Don't be afraid.

98
00:08:46,519 --> 00:08:47,679
Don't be like a baby.

99
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:05,000
No, buddy.

100
00:09:05,330 --> 00:09:06,759
Are you playing with the water?

101
00:09:08,210 --> 00:09:09,360
You must really be afraid of water.

102
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:10,360
Come on.

103
00:09:12,210 --> 00:09:13,759
Just don't torture yourself.

104
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,679
No. I like to torture myself.

105
00:09:16,960 --> 00:09:17,960
I like that.

106
00:09:19,090 --> 00:09:20,720
Actually, the water isn't scary.

107
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:21,799
The only fear...

108
00:09:21,919 --> 00:09:22,960
is fear itself.

109
00:09:23,279 --> 00:09:24,799
Come on, beat it. Try again.

110
00:09:25,879 --> 00:09:26,919
You can do it.

111
00:09:42,720 --> 00:09:44,519
What is it this time?

112
00:09:45,960 --> 00:09:47,279
I think this fear...

113
00:09:47,840 --> 00:09:49,090
is too terrifying.

114
00:09:51,559 --> 00:09:52,879
Forget it. I'll try next time.

115
00:10:14,559 --> 00:10:15,600
Next time?

116
00:10:15,720 --> 00:10:16,720
Take care.

117
00:11:00,240 --> 00:11:01,240
Hello.

118
00:11:02,919 --> 00:11:04,240
How was your day today?

119
00:11:05,960 --> 00:11:07,200
Not bad.

120
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,559
I wanted to learn to swim, but I was still too afraid.

121
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,639
Why do you suddenly want to learn how to swim?

122
00:11:13,919 --> 00:11:16,639
There's no misunderstanding anymore, right?

123
00:11:16,639 --> 00:11:19,679
And it's embarrassing not knowing how to swim.

124
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:22,720
I'm afraid it'll affect future rescue missions in the water.

125
00:11:25,039 --> 00:11:26,679
Don't rush. Take it slow.

126
00:11:28,039 --> 00:11:30,639
This kind of fear can't go away in a mere day or two.

127
00:11:31,879 --> 00:11:34,480
Yes, so I'm slowly getting rid of it now.

128
00:11:36,799 --> 00:11:38,080
How about this?

129
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,480
Call me your teacher. I'll teach you.

130
00:11:40,600 --> 00:11:41,600
You'll teach me?

131
00:11:43,679 --> 00:11:45,080
You should have told me earlier.

132
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,679
We'll start tomorrow then.

133
00:11:47,799 --> 00:11:50,279
Go and prepare a nice swimsuit.

134
00:11:53,000 --> 00:11:55,840
Who said I have to wear a swimsuit to teach you swimming?

135
00:11:57,159 --> 00:11:58,320
Then what will you wear?

136
00:11:59,000 --> 00:12:00,919
We'll see.

137
00:12:08,679 --> 00:12:09,919
- Hello? - Hello?

138
00:12:10,240 --> 00:12:11,399
Hello, can you hear me?

139
00:12:11,879 --> 00:12:12,919
Hello?

140
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:24,240
What's wrong with this phone?

141
00:12:37,679 --> 00:12:40,120
Why are you being so mysterious?

142
00:12:52,840 --> 00:12:54,080
I want to talk to you.

143
00:12:55,080 --> 00:12:56,080
I feel upset.

144
00:13:01,000 --> 00:13:02,559
Hey, what's wrong?

145
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,840
I have a question.

146
00:13:07,039 --> 00:13:08,080
Tell me.

147
00:13:09,279 --> 00:13:10,320
There's a person...

148
00:13:11,120 --> 00:13:12,399
who hurt you,

149
00:13:14,240 --> 00:13:15,440
but you still like him.

150
00:13:16,159 --> 00:13:17,200
What would you do?

151
00:13:20,080 --> 00:13:21,960
No way. Do you love him that much?

152
00:13:23,039 --> 00:13:24,600
But he doesn't want to marry you.

153
00:13:34,799 --> 00:13:36,480
However,

154
00:13:38,120 --> 00:13:39,879
a lot of things are changing.

155
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:44,519
For example, Hou Jue and his dad...

156
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:46,159
are getting along now.

157
00:13:46,799 --> 00:13:48,080
So...

158
00:13:49,519 --> 00:13:50,600
it's hard to say.

159
00:13:54,879 --> 00:13:56,679
Is it because his dad fell ill?

160
00:13:57,559 --> 00:13:58,559
Maybe.

161
00:13:59,320 --> 00:14:01,840
After he fell ill, it seems like they've both changed.

162
00:14:03,879 --> 00:14:06,039
Now, they have to fight together...

163
00:14:06,759 --> 00:14:08,240
or the company may go bankrupt.

164
00:14:10,759 --> 00:14:11,759
Bankrupt?

165
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,480
Shi Yi.

166
00:14:17,799 --> 00:14:19,000
That's all for now.

167
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:21,080
- I have something to do. Bye. - I...

168
00:14:23,600 --> 00:14:25,360
Why is she so strange?

169
00:14:32,279 --> 00:14:33,279
(Old Man)

170
00:15:04,159 --> 00:15:06,279
Why did you ask me to come so urgently?

171
00:15:12,519 --> 00:15:14,519
I heard about what happened to you.

172
00:15:16,600 --> 00:15:17,960
Why didn't you tell me?

173
00:15:18,399 --> 00:15:19,399
I...

174
00:15:22,679 --> 00:15:24,360
Are you talking about me getting hospitalized?

175
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:27,279
I've already been discharged.

176
00:15:27,279 --> 00:15:28,840
Look how healthy I am.

177
00:15:29,679 --> 00:15:31,080
I'm talking about your company.

178
00:15:38,080 --> 00:15:39,159
That...

179
00:15:40,200 --> 00:15:41,840
That has passed too.

180
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:43,759
Initially,

181
00:15:44,399 --> 00:15:47,360
all I thought about was work, day in and day out.

182
00:15:47,360 --> 00:15:49,519
But It's great now.

183
00:15:50,519 --> 00:15:52,519
I just eat and sleep every day.

184
00:15:52,759 --> 00:15:54,480
I even enjoy a warm shower at night.

185
00:15:54,879 --> 00:15:55,879
Things are good.

186
00:15:56,840 --> 00:15:58,519
I don't want to have to hear about you...

187
00:15:59,799 --> 00:16:00,919
from other people.

188
00:16:10,000 --> 00:16:12,639
I want to go back to how we used to be.

189
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,200
Qian Qian.

190
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,360
It's all in the past.

191
00:16:25,360 --> 00:16:26,919
We can't go back to how we used to be.

192
00:16:27,039 --> 00:16:28,039
Old man.

193
00:16:43,039 --> 00:16:45,120
Qian Qian, don't call me "old man" anymore, okay?

194
00:16:46,039 --> 00:16:47,039
Don't call me that anymore.

195
00:16:49,720 --> 00:16:51,320
I've healed a bit now.

196
00:16:51,320 --> 00:16:53,360
I don't want to think about the past anymore.

197
00:16:54,080 --> 00:16:55,679
Isn't Hai Xing a nice guy?

198
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:57,600
He's young...

199
00:16:58,679 --> 00:17:00,159
and he's devoted to you.

200
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,320
You should cherish him.

201
00:17:02,759 --> 00:17:04,650
I've already clearly rejected him.

202
00:17:05,119 --> 00:17:06,480
It's not possible between us.

203
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:12,440
It's the same for us.

204
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:22,480
If there's nothing else,

205
00:17:23,279 --> 00:17:24,279
I'll get going.

206
00:17:28,599 --> 00:17:29,599
Don't go.

207
00:17:31,200 --> 00:17:32,279
Qian Qian.

208
00:17:33,759 --> 00:17:36,039
You still have a long future ahead of you.

209
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:40,170
You deserve a better life.

210
00:17:40,319 --> 00:17:42,519
My life won't be better off without you.

211
00:17:44,359 --> 00:17:46,680
Qian Qian, I'm old now.

212
00:17:46,680 --> 00:17:48,359
I have nothing.

213
00:17:48,480 --> 00:17:49,960
I have no money.

214
00:17:50,440 --> 00:17:52,240
What's the point of being with me?

215
00:17:53,319 --> 00:17:54,650
If we keep going,

216
00:17:54,650 --> 00:17:57,000
I'll only drag you down with me and be a burden to you.

217
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,650
And I definitely won't allow myself to do this.

218
00:17:59,920 --> 00:18:01,440
You're not a burden to me.

219
00:18:01,759 --> 00:18:03,119
I can do everything.

220
00:18:03,279 --> 00:18:04,480
I can take care of you.

221
00:18:04,799 --> 00:18:06,359
I...

222
00:18:08,039 --> 00:18:10,000
Compared to the old Mr. Hou,

223
00:18:10,519 --> 00:18:11,720
I...

224
00:18:11,720 --> 00:18:13,240
I love the current you even more.

225
00:18:13,440 --> 00:18:14,839
You know how to do everything.

226
00:18:15,890 --> 00:18:18,319
You're currently living an idealistic life.

227
00:18:18,599 --> 00:18:20,480
I'm living in reality.

228
00:18:20,680 --> 00:18:22,960
I know how harsh reality is.

229
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,650
If you continue being with me,

230
00:18:29,890 --> 00:18:31,480
you'll have to face a lot of pressure.

231
00:18:32,559 --> 00:18:34,680
When I had money, I had confidence.

232
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:36,440
But I have nothing now.

233
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:40,200
Your old man has no confidence now.

234
00:18:40,759 --> 00:18:42,039
Let me ask you one more thing.

235
00:18:42,039 --> 00:18:43,960
How will you explain this to your parents?

236
00:18:43,960 --> 00:18:45,799
Your parents don't know about my situation right now.

237
00:18:45,799 --> 00:18:47,599
How will you explain this to your friends?

238
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:49,359
Tell me. How will you explain it?

239
00:18:49,519 --> 00:18:51,759
I don't care what other people think.

240
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:54,079
I care.

241
00:18:55,240 --> 00:18:57,440
I care. I can't do this anymore.

242
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:01,279
I just want to live the rest of my life in peace now.

243
00:19:13,119 --> 00:19:14,559
I swore to the heavens...

244
00:19:16,839 --> 00:19:18,119
that in my next life,

245
00:19:20,119 --> 00:19:22,200
I have to meet this girl again.

246
00:19:27,359 --> 00:19:30,200
I have to meet her 20 years earlier.

